{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"688bc44b-34a9-4be5-88d1-581294f1c163","content":"Here's what I found in `my_app/views.py`:\n\n**Line 3** — `datetime.now()` ⚠️ untestable static call\n\nThis is hard to mock in tests because it's called directly inside the function. You can't control the return value without patching.\n\n**Recommended fix — use Django's `timezone.now()` + dependency injection:**\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request, now_func=timezone.now):\n    now = now_func()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nOr, at minimum, switch to `django.utils.timezone.now()` which is easier to patch with `freezegun` or `unittest.mock.patch`:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\n**Summary:** Only 1 file, 1 occurrence of an untestable static found. The project is small — this is a quick fix. `timezone.now()` also adds timezone awareness, which `datetime.now()` lacks.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c1aabff2-f09e-49f1-ab82-f547134f1f95","outputTokens":275,"requestId":"0424:28DE61:1D5BD28:215C736:69E83393"},"id":"81ac4661-eead-4567-a13f-c1ec363bee89","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:34:02.013Z","parentId":"b04f0ab2-066d-4899-8adc-e61b358d6ad9"}
